=Post-production=
During editing, filmmakers tried to remake Hawking's synthesised voice, but it did not turn out as they wanted. Hawking enjoyed the film enough that he granted them permission to use his own synthesised voice, which is heard in the final film.<ref>cite web|last=Setoodeh|first=Ramin|title=How Eddie Redmayne became Stephen Hawking in 'The Theory of Everything'|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/eddie-redmayne-theory-of-everything-stephen-hawking-1201340498/ |website=Variety.com|publisher=Variety (magazine)|Variety|accessdate=24 February 2015</ref>

Historical accuracy
The film takes various dramatic liberties with the history it portrays. Writing for the film blog of UK daily newspaper ''The Guardian'', Michelle Dean noted: quote|''The Theory of Everything'''s marketing materials will tell you it is based on Jane Hawking's memoir of her marriage, a book published in the UK as ''Music to Move the Stars'', and then re-issued as ''Travelling to Infinity''. But the screenwriters rearranged the facts to suit certain dramatic conventions.  And while that always happens in these based-on-a-true-story films, the scale of the departure in ''The Theory of Everything'' is unusually wide. The film becomes almost dishonestendashin a way that feels unfair to both parties, and oddly, particularly Jane Hawking herself.<ref name=GuardianDisservice>cite web |url=https://www.TheGuardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/nov/14/theory-of-everything-movie-jane-steven-hawking-memoir|title=The Theory of Everything does Jane Hawking a disservice |last=Dean |first=Michelle |date=14 November 2014 |website=TheGuardian.com |publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=19 November 2016</ref>  In ''Slate (magazine)|Slate'', L.V. Anderson wrote that "the Stephen played by Eddie Redmayne is far gentler and more sensitive" than suggested in ''Travelling to Infinity''.<ref name=SlateAccurate>cite web |url=http://www.Slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2014/11/07/the_theory_of_everything_how_accurate_is_the_new_stephen_hawking_movie_starring.html |title=How accurate is The Theory of Everything? |last=Anderson|first=L.V.|date=7 November 2014|website=Slate.com|publisher=''Slate (magazine)|Slate''|accessdate=19 November 2016</ref> The ''Slate'' article further noted that the character Brian, Hawking's closest friend at Cambridge in the film, is not based on a real individual, but rather a composite of several of his real-life friends.<ref name=SlateAccurate/>

The film alters some of the details surrounding the beginning of Stephen and Jane's relationship, including how they met, as well as the fact that Jane knew about Stephen's disease before they started dating.<ref name=GuardianDisservice/> ''Slate'' also comments that the film underplays Hawking's stubbornness and refusal to accept outside assistance for his disorder.<ref name=SlateAccurate/>

For ''The Guardian'', Dean concluded by saying: quote|The movie presents the demise of their relationship as a beautiful, tear-soaked, mutually respectful conversation.  Of course that didn't actually happen either. Jane's book describes a protracted breakup that comes to a head in a screaming fight on vacation. She also described devastation when Hawking announced by letter he was leaving her for his second wife, Elaine Mason. He ended up married to Mason for 10 years before that fell apart, and then he and Jane mended fences. Which, as it happens, the movie fudges too. It tries to present the rapprochement as coming when Hawking was made a Companion of Honour in 1989, but that actually happened before the couple separated.<ref name=GuardianDisservice/>

Physicist Adrian Melott, a former student of Dennis W. Sciama|Dennis Sciama, Hawking's doctoral supervisor portrayed in the film, strongly criticised the portrayal of Sciama in the film.<ref>cite journal|title=Views: The Theory of Everything is missing something: letter from Adrian L Melott|last=Melott|first=Adrian L. |url=http://AstroGeo.OxfordJournals.org/content/56/2/2.9.3.full|year=2015|website=AstroGeo.OxfordJournals.org|publisher=Astronomy & Geophysics |volume=56 |issue=2 |page=2.9|doi=10.1093/astrogeo/atv057|accessdate=19 November 2016</ref>

In the film, when Stephen attends the opera in Geneva, his companion was actually Raymond LaFlamme, his PhD student.

Release
On 8 October 2013, Universal Pictures International had acquired the rights to distribute the film internationally.<ref name=HollywoodReporterChild/>

On 10 April 2014, Focus Features acquired the distribution rights to ''The Theory of Everything'' in the United States, with the plan of a 2014 limited theatrical release.<ref>cite web|last=|first=|title=The Theory of Everything|url=http://www.TIFF.net/festivals/thefestival/programmes/specialpresentations/theory-of-everything|date=9 October 2013|website=TIFF.net|publisher=Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF)|accessdate=9 October 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140726191339/http://www.tiff.net/festivals/thefestival/programmes/specialpresentations/theory-of-everything|archivedate=26 July 2014|df=dmy-all</ref> publisher after, Entertainment One Films picked up the Canadian distribution rights.<ref>cite web|last=|first=|title=The Theory of Everything – 2015 film|url=http://www.EFilmsWorld.com/the-theory-of-everything-film-2015.html|date=9 October 2013|website=EFilmsWorld.com|publisher=EFilmsWorld|accessdate=9 October 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826115318/http://www.efilmsworld.com/the-theory-of-everything-film-2015.html|archivedate=26 August 2014|df=dmy-all</ref> The first Trailer (promotion)|trailer of the film was released on 7 August 2014.<ref>cite web|last=Child|first=Ben|title=First trailer revealed for Stephen Hawking biopic The Theory of Everything |url=https://www.TheGuardian.com/film/2014/aug/07/stephen-hawking-biopic-first-trailer-the-theory-of-everything|date=7 August 2014 |website=TheGuardian.com|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=7 August 2014</ref><ref>cite web|last=Child|first=Ben|title=FTIFF: Eddie Redmayne is Stephen Hawking in trailer for 'The Theory of Everything'|url=http://www.SoundOnSight.org/tiff-eddie-redmayne-is-stephen-hawking-in-trailer-for-the-theory-of-everything/ |date=6 August 2014|website=SoundOnSight.org|publisher=Sound On Sight|accessdate=6 August 2014</ref>

''The Theory of Everything'' premiered at the 2014 Toronto International Film Festival|Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF)<ref name=WorkingTitleFilms118/> on 7 September 2014,<ref>cite web|last= |first= |title=Toronto film festival 2014: full lineup |url=https://www.TheGuardian.com/film/2014/jul/22/toronto-film-festival-2014-full-line-up|date=29 July 2014|website=TheGuardian.com|publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=29 July 2014</ref> where it opened in the official sidebar section, Special Presentations.<ref name=VarietyFormula>cite web|title=Toronto: 'Theory of Everything' has the right formula for Oscars|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/awards/theory-of-everything-has-the-right-formula-for-oscars-1201300377/|date=7 September 2014|website=Variety.com|publisher=Variety (magazine)|Variety|accessdate=7 September 2014</ref><ref>cite news|last=Child|first=Ben|title=Toronto Film Festival lineup includes Denzel Washington's 'Equalizer,' Kate Winslet's 'A Little Chaos'|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/tiff-toronto-intl-film-festival-gala-special-presentations-1201266480/|date=22 July 2014|website=Variety.com|publisher=Variety (magazine)|Variety|accessdate=22 July 2014</ref>

The film had a limited release in the United States on 7 November 2014,<ref>cite news|last=McNary|first=Dave|title=Stephen Hawking biopic 'Theory of Everything' set for Nov. 7 launch|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/stephen-hawking-biopic-theory-of-everything-set-for-nov-7-launch-1201155537/|date=10 April 2014|website=Variety.com|publisher=Variety (magazine)|Variety|accessdate=11 April 2014</ref> expanded in successive weeks to Taiwan, Austria, and Germany,<ref>cite web|last= |first= |title=Focus' 'Theory of Everything' set for November; relativity dates 'November Man' for August; Disneynature's 'Monkey Kingdom' due in 2015|url=http://Deadline.com/2014/04/stephen-hawking-movie-theory-of-everything-release-date-november-7-2014-712736/|date=10 April 2014 |website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=10 April 2014</ref> ahead of a United Kingdom release on 1 January 2015, before being released throughout Europe.<ref>cite news|last=Child|first=Ben|title=Stephen Hawking biopic The Theory of Everything trailer released, movie stars Eddie Redmayne |url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/566822/stephen-hawking-biopic-the-theory-of-everything-trailer-released-movie-stars-eddie-redmayne-watch|date=6 August 2014 |website=uk.eonline.com|publisher=E! Online|accessdate=6 August 2014</ref>

Reception
=Box office=
''The Theory of Everything'' earned $122,873,310 worldwide, with its biggest markets coming from North America ($35.9 million), and the United Kingdom ($31.9 million).<ref name=BOM/> The film had a North American limited release on 7 November 2014; it was released in five theatres, and earned $207,000 on its opening weekend, for an average of $41,400 per theatre. The film was then Wide release|widely released on 26 November across 802 theatres, earning US$5 million, and debuting at No. 7 at the Box Office. During its five-day Thanksgiving (United States)|Thanksgiving week, the film earned $6.4 million.<ref>cite web |url=http://Deadline.com/2014/11/theory-of-everything-expands-with-gusto-amid-huge-imitation-game-opening-1201303097/|title='Theory of Everything' expands with gusto amid huge 'imitation game' opening|author=Brian Brooks|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=30 November 2014 |accessdate=1 December 2014</ref>

=Critical response=
Film review aggregator Rotten Tomatoes reports an approval rating of 79% based on 236 reviews, with an average rating of 7.3/10. The site's critical consensus reads, "Part biopic, part love story, ''The Theory of Everything'' rises on James Marsh's polished direction and the strength of its two leads."<ref>cite web |title=The Theory of Everything (2014)|url=http://www.RottenTomatoes.com/m/theory_of_everything_2015/|website=RottenTomatoes.com|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=13 February 2015</ref> Metacritic assigned the film a weighted average score of 72 out of 100, based on 47 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>cite web|title=The Theory of Everything (2014)|url=http://www.Metacritic.com/movie/the-theory-of-everything|accessdate=30 December 2014 |website=Metacritic.com|publisher=Metacritic|date=14 November 2014</ref>

Catherine Shoard of ''The Guardian'' wrote, "Redmayne towers: this is an astonishing, genuinely visceral performance which bears comparison with Daniel Day-Lewis in ''My Left Foot''".<ref>cite web|title=The Theory of Everything review: Hawking's story packs powerful punch |url=https://www.TheGuardian.com/film/2014/sep/07/theory-of-everything-review-hawking-eddie-redmayne |date=7 September 2014|website=TheGuardian.com|publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=7 September 2014</ref>  Lou Lumenick, in his review for ''The New York Post'', called the film "tremendously moving and inspirational".<ref>cite web|title=This Stephen Hawking biopic is a good bet for Oscar nods|url=https://nypost.com/2014/09/08/this-stephen-hawking-biopic-is-a-good-bet-for-oscar-nods/|date=8 September 2014|website=nypost.com|publisher=The New York Post|accessdate=8 September 2014</ref>  Justin Chang of ''Variety (magazine)|Variety'' remarked, "A stirring and bittersweet love story, inflected with tasteful good humor...."  He continued by praising the "superb performances" from Redmayne and Jones, as well commenting very positively about Jóhannsson's score, "whose arpeggio-like repetitions and progressions at times evoke the compositions of Philip Glass", whilst praising John Paul Kelly's production design, and Steven Noble's costumes.<ref>cite web |title=Toronto film review: 'The Theory of Everything'|url=https://variety.com/?p=1201300258|date=7 September 2014|website=Variety.com|publisher=Variety (magazine)|Variety|accessdate=7 September 2014</ref>  Leslie Felperin of ''The Hollywood Reporter'' remarked, "A solid, duly moving account of their complicated relationship, spanning roughly 25 years, and made with impeccable professional polish", praising Delhomme's cinematography as having "lush, intricately lit compositions", and adding "a splendor that keeps the film consistently watchable", and Jóhannsson's score as "dainty precision with a ineffable scientific quality about it".<ref>cite web|title='The Theory of Everything': Toronto review|url=http://www.HollywoodReporter.com/review/theory-everything-toronto-review-730837|date=7 September 2014|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=7 September 2014</ref>  ''The Daily Telegraph'''s Tim Robey granted the film a positive review, stating that, "In its potted appraisal of Hawking's cosmology, ''The Theory of Everything'' bends over backwards to speak to the layman, and relies on plenty of second-hand inspiration.  But it borrows from the right sources, this theory.  And that's something", while praising Redmayne's performance, McCarten's script, and Delhomme's cinematography.<ref>cite web|title=The Theory of Everything, review: 'tasteful and affecting': Toronto review|url=http://www.Telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/toronto-film-festival/11081593/The-Theory-of-Everything-review-tasteful-and-affecting.html|date=8 September 2014|website=Telegraph.co.uk|publisher=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=8 September 2014</ref>  ''Deadline Hollywood'''s Pete Hammond marked McCarten's script and Marsh's direction for praise, and of the film's Toronto reception, wrote: "To say the response here was rapturous would not be understating the enthusiasm I heard — not just from pundits, but also Academy voters with whom I spoke.  One told me he came in with high expectations for a quality movie, and this one exceeded them".<ref name=DeadlineOscar/>

The film was not without its detractors.  Some criticised Marsh's focus on Hawking's romantic life.  Alonso Duralde of ''The Wrap'' stated that "Hawking's innovations and refusal to subscribe to outdated modes of thinking merely underscore the utter conventionality of his film biography".<ref>cite web |url=http://www.TheWrap.com/the-theory-of-everything-review-eddie-redmayne-stephen-hawking/|title='The Theory of Everything' review: Eddie Redmayne gives body and soul to a by-the-numbers biopic|website=TheWrap.com|publisher=The Wrap|first=Alonso|last=Duralde|date=8 September 2014|accessdate=11 November 2014</ref> Eric Kohn of ''Indiewire'' added that "James Marsh's biopic salutes the famous physicist's commitment, but falls short of exploring his brilliant ideas".<ref>cite web|url=http://www.Indiewire.com/article/toronto-review-eddie-redmayne-and-felicity-jones-salvage-stephen-hawking-biopic-the-theory-of-everything-20140908 |title=Toronto review: Eddie Redmayne and Felicity Jones salvage Stephen Hawking biopic 'The Theory of Everything' |website=Indiewire.com |publisher=Indiewire |first=Eric|last=Kohn|date=8 September 2014|accessdate=11 November 2014</ref>  Dennis Overbye of the ''New York Times'' noted: quote|The movie doesn't deserve any prizes for its drive-by muddling of Dr. Hawking's scientific work, leaving viewers in the dark about exactly why he is so famous. Instead of showing how he undermined traditional notions of space and time, it panders to religious sensibilities about what his work does or does not say about the existence of God, which in fact is very little.<ref name=NYT-20141028-DO>cite web|last=Overbye|first=Dennis|authorlink=Dennis Overbye|title=The leaky science of Hollywood – Stephen Hawking's movie life story is not very scientific|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/10/28/science/stephen-hawkings-movie-life-story-is-not-very-scientific.html|date=28 October 2014|website=nytimes.com|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=28 October 2014</ref>  Writing for ''The Guardian'''s film blog, Michelle Dean argues that the film does a disservice to Jane Wilde Hawking, by "rearrang[ing] the facts to suit certain dramatic conventions... ''The Theory of Everything'' is hell-bent on preserving the cliche".<ref>cite web|last=Dean|first=Michelle|title=The Theory of Everything does Jane Hawking a disservice|url=https://www.TheGuardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/nov/14/theory-of-everything-movie-jane-steven-hawking-memoir|website=TheGuardian.com|publisher=The Guardian|date=14 November 2014|accessdate=14 November 2014</ref>

The film's producers, writer, director Marsh, and actors Redmayne and Jones were widely favoured for award season success.<ref name=VarietyFormula/><ref name=DeadlineOscar>cite web|title=Toronto: 'Theory of Everything' sends Oscar race into early overdrive as TIFF world premieres keep on coming |url=http://Deadline.com/2014/09/toronto-theory-of-everything-sends-oscar-race-into-early-overdrive-as-tiff-world-premieres-keep-on-coming-831028/|date=8 September 2014|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=8 September 2014</ref><ref>cite web|title=TIFF: Stephen Hawking story 'The Theory of Everything' spurs Oscar talk|url=http://InsideMovies.ew.com/2014/09/07/stephen-hawking-theory-of-everything-spurs-oscar-buzz/|date=7 September 2014 |website=InsideMovies.ew.com|publisher=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=7 September 2014</ref><ref>cite web|title=Toronto: Eddie Redmayne leaps to head of Oscar pack for 'Theory of Everything'|url=http://www.HollywoodReporter.com/race/toronto-eddie-redmayne-leaps-head-730941|date=7 September 2014 |work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=7 September 2014</ref>

=Accolades=
Main|List of accolades received by The Theory of Everything
''The Theory of Everything'' received several awards and nominations following its release.  At the 87th Academy Awards, it was nominated in the categories of Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture, Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor for Eddie Redmayne, Academy Award for Best Actress|Best Actress for Jones, Academy Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay for McCarten, and Academy Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score for Jóhann Jóhannsson; with Eddie Redmayne winning the film's sole Academy Award for his performance. The film was nominated for ten British Academy Film Awards,<ref>cite web|url=http://Deadline.com/2015/01/bafta-nominations-2015-baftas-nominees-full-list-1201344262/|title=BAFTA nominations: 'Grand Budapest Hotel' leads with 11 – full list|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=8 January 2015 |accessdate=9 January 2015</ref> (winning for Best Adapted Screenplay, Best British Film, and Best Actor), five Critics' Choice Movie Awards,<ref>cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/birdman-grand-budapest-pace-noms-for-critics-choice-awards-1201379383/|title='Birdman', 'Grand Budapest' top Critics Choice awards nominations|website=Variety.com|publisher=Variety (magazine)|Variety|date=15 December 2014|first=Tim|last=Gray|accessdate=15 December 2014</ref> and three Screen Actors Guild Awards.<ref>cite web|title=Nominees nnnounced for the 21st Annual Screen Actors Guild Awards |url=http://www.SAGawards.org/media-pr/press-releases/nominees-announced-21st-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards%C2%AE|website=SAGawards.org|publisher=SAG-AFTRA |date=10 December 2014 |accessdate=10 December 2014</ref>  At the 72nd Golden Globe Awards, Redmayne won Golden Globe Award for Best Actor - Motion Picture Drama|Best Actor – Motion Picture Drama, and Jóhannsson won Golden Globe Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score.  The film, and Jones were also nominated.  Production designer John Paul Kelly earned a nomination for Excellence in Production Design for a Period Film from the Art Directors Guild,<ref>cite web|url=http://Deadline.com/2015/01/birdman-foxcatcher-among-art-directors-guild-nominees-1201341121/|title='Birdman', 'Foxcatcher' among Art Directors Guild nominees|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=5 January 2015|accessdate=5 January 2015</ref> while the producers were nominated for Best Theatrical Motion Picture by the Producers Guild of America.<ref>cite web|url=http://Deadline.com/2015/01/american-sniper-birdman-boyhood-pga-awards-nominees-full-list-1201341195/|title='American Sniper,' 'Birdman' & 'Boyhood' among PGA awards nominees |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=5 January 2015|accessdate=5 January 2015</ref>

